Program: The History Hour
Title: The German American Bund
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04tbvfq
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 26 Feb 2017
In the 1930s, a group of German-American Nazi sympathisers known as the German American Bund held rallies and summer camps across the US. Also, the lawyers who helped Serbian leader Slobodan Milosevic defend himself against war crimes charges and how vandals attacked Denmark's famous Little Mermaid Statue. Show less